column168: THE SPILL WAS CONFIRMED AS ONLY THE NITRIC ACID DRUM. WE NEUTRALIZED ALL ACID WHICH CONTACTED THE GROUND USING SODA ASH. THIS INCLUDED THE WATER USED TO FLUSH THE ACID VAPORS FOM THE TRUCK TO ALLOW ENTRY INTO THE BOX TO STOP THE LEAKAGE AND CONTAIN UNSPILLED MATERIAL. THE WATER ON THE GROUND WA S CHECKED FOR PH AND SUCTIONED ONTO A VACUM TRUCK WE BROUGHT TO THE SITE. TOTAL COLLECTED WAS 200 GALLONS. THE BACK OF THE TRUCK WAS NEUTRALIZED WITH SODA ASH AND RESIDUE DRUMMED FOR LEGAL DISPOSAL. IN OUR OPINION WHICH WAS SHARED BY THE DEM REPRESENTATIVE ON THE SITE, THERE WAS NO ENVIROMENTAL DAM AGE, THE PARKING LOT AND SEWERS WERE UNEFFECTED AND THE SPILL WAS COMPLETEL Y REMEDIATED IN ACCORDANCE WITH DOT, EPA AND STATE REGULATIONS.
